# Node/npm commands: container-only (shared)

## Rule (hard)
- **Never run `node`, `npm`, or `npx` on the host machine** when assisting with containerized projects.
  - Host Node/npm may be missing or a different version than the container image.
  - Running on host can lead to non-reproducible behavior, flaky CI parity, and accidental dependency drift.

## Runbook

See `node-npm-container-only` skill.
